description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you an experienced operational manager looking to try a new specialty?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you an aspiring manager looking for the next exciting opportunity to showcase your skills and abilities?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Division of Neurosciences and MSK is currently recruiting a Performance and Operational Manager, Band 7 to cover Cluster 2 Specialities (Trauma and Elective Orthopaedics).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a proactive, enthusiastic and hard-working manager to oversee the operational delivery of these services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is pivotal in making sure we meet all performance targets, including RTT by; keeping close scrutiny of patient tracking lists and ensuring optimum utilisation of Outpatients and Theatre capacity. The post-holder will be line managing 3 support managers and work closely with senior management team managing clinical, nursing and AHP staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have the opportunity to be involved in strategic projects and service improvements depending on the experience you bring to the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will have experience in; performance management, managing complex processes, setting and communicating a clear direction, building and maintaining effective working relationships and providing support to team members from all professional backgrounds in order to ensure that the best service is given to our patients. Financial acumen, leading teams and service improvement experience is desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Harriet Narey&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: General Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: harriet.narey@nbt.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Harriet Narey - General Manager for Trauma &amp; Orthopaedics (Harriet.Narey@nbt.nhs.uk)&lt;/p&gt;
